# Advantages of JavaScript

* Easy to learn and use
* Fast execution in browsers
* Makes web pages interactive
* Supported by all modern browsers
* Platform independent
* Reduces server load
* Supports client-side scripting
* Used for frontend and backend development
* Large community support
* Rich libraries and frameworks available
* Supports asynchronous programming
* Easy integration with HTML and CSS
* Helps create dynamic web applications
* Open-source language
* Lightweight programming language

---

# Limitations of JavaScript

* Security issues in client-side scripting
* Different browser behaviors may cause compatibility issues
* Cannot directly access system files
* Debugging can be difficult sometimes
* Slower than compiled languages
* Single-threaded language
* Code can be visible to users in browsers
* Limited multithreading support
* Dependent on browser support
* Large applications can become complex to manage
